<HEADLINE>
<P>
ADOLPH L. ANTONIO; AEROSPACE EXECUTIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Adolph L. Antonio, 80, an aerospace executive who headed the solid rocket 
propulsion division of Aerojet General in the 1940s and 1950s. In 1954, he left 
Southern California to take over the chemical division of General Tire & Rubber 
Co., Aerojet's parent company, in Akron, Ohio, returning as general manager of 
Aerojet's Space General Corp. In Arcadia on Wednesday of cancer. 
</P>
