<HEADLINE>
<P>
OLYMPIC SPIRIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For two weeks, we have been spoiled by the gallant acts of courage, 
sportsmanship, and competition. The world has come together, embraced by the 
sheer joy of the Olympic spirit.For two weeks we were one world, once again. 
But now that the majestic harmony of the Olympics has come to an end, it sure 
will be good to get back to the bloodshed in Bosnia, the endless fighting in 
the Middle East, the starvation in Somalia, and the senseless violence raging 
on here at home. Geez, was it just youthful optimism, or for a brief second, 
did I actually believe that the world could really get along together? 
</P>
<P>
 For two weeks, we've watched athletes, coaches and fans from around the globe 
descend upon a gracious and peaceful Norwegian village. For two weeks, we have 
witnessed the best that man has to offer. Let us bottle some of that Olympic 
spirit -- full of peace, goodwill and love. Please, let's take a lesson from 
our athletes and begin our long march towards peace. In the words of Olympic 
President Juan Antonio Samaranch, "Please stop killing. Drop your guns, 
please." 
</P>
<P>
 JEFF GREEN 
</P>
<P>
 La Jolla 
</P>
