<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAR INSURANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Here is a recommendation for dealing with the problem of uninsured motorists: 
</P>
<P>
 If you do not have auto insurance, then you automatically forfeit your right 
to sue another motorist for damages in the event of an accident regardless of 
who is at fault. 
</P>
<P>
 Although it is not a complete solution, it would reduce litigation and 
encourage those now uninsured, to get insurance. It would also bring a sense of 
fairness to those who do buy insurance. 
</P>
<P>
 BILL SIMON 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
