<HEADLINE>
<P>
SIGNS OF TV'S TIMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 This is a little late, but I feel this has to be put in print: It is 
understandable that television news needs those man-on-the-street reports. But 
to watch people mob around a TV reporter and acting crazy and members of gangs 
showing their gang signs is deplorable. 
</P>
<P>
 When a Channel 7 reporter was interviewing some people who were possibly 
becoming homeless because of the Northridge earthquake, they were nervous, but 
otherwise calm, because of the ordeal. But, in the background, there were 
people dancing around, like it's a party, showing their gang symbols, showing 
no respect to the people being interviewed. 
</P>
<P>
 I feel that the news producers -- of all networks -- should show common sense 
and black out that interview and switch to another area. We have enough 
problems with gangs in this great city, so why should we glorify them by 
showing their rudeness? 
</P>
<P>
 MEL STAZOFF 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress 
</P>
</TEXT>
