<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND TV; OLYMPIAN KERRIGAN WILL HOST 'SATURDAY NIGHT LIVE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Olympic silver medalist Nancy Kerrigan goes from the ice to the stage tonight 
as host of "Saturday Night Live," 11:30 p.m. on NBC (Channels 4, 36 and 
39).Aretha Franklin is the musical guest. 
</P>
<P>
 On Sunday at 10 a.m., KABC-TV Channel 7 will launch "Vista L.A.," a weekly 
half-hour show that will present the Latino perspective on issues and events in 
Southern California. Henry Alfaro and Laura Diaz are the hosts. 
</P>
<P>
 Whitewater will be the dominate topic on the public affairs shows this 
weekend. N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
