<HEADLINE>
<P>
AVERAGE SPENDING FOR MEDICARE RISES 8.7% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Medicare spent $3,940 on average last year for each of its 36 million elderly 
or disabled beneficiaries, the government reported Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 That figure represented an 8.7% increase from the year before. The growth rate 
was down from 11.5% in fiscal 1992, the Health Care Financing Administration 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Total Medicare benefit payments in fiscal 1993 were $142.9 billion, or 10.6% 
more than the earlier year. The total payments grew at a faster rate in part 
because of a 1.7% increase in the number of people enrolled in Medicare. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
