<HEADLINE>
<P>
99-YEAR TERM FOR FATAL FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man who pleaded guilty to setting a fire that killed three women at a 
retirement home has been sentenced to 99 years in prison. Paul Kenneth Keller, 
28, who was sentenced Thursday, already is serving a 75-year prison term after 
pleading guilty last May to setting 32 fires and admitting that he set 44 
others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
