<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAKER COACH PFUND IS GIVEN ONE-YEAR CONTRACT EXTENSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HOWARD-COOPER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coach Randy Pfund and the Lakers have signed a one-year contract extension, it 
was announced Friday, a move he realizes guarantees financial security through 
1995-96 but not job security. 
</P>
<P>
 Owner Jerry Buss approached Pfund after last season and said he wanted to talk 
about adding a year to the contract, then reiterated that during training camp 
by saying he wanted to have Pfund around "in some capacity."But after 
discussing the reassignment provision, the sides agreed to a standard 
coaching-only deal. 
</P>
<P>
 "That means something to me personally," Pfund said. "I've been in the 
organization. I was hired to be head coach. Without going overboard on it and 
trying to pin too much too it, because I'm a realistic person, I think it 
showed there is some confidence in our management in what I've tried to do the 
last year and a half. I think you can leave it at that. 
</P>
<P>
 "If something else happens at another point in time and they have interest in 
me doing something else within the organization, that would be another 
arrangement." SCOTT HOWARD-COOPER 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA031294-0151 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 022040 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
March 12, 1994, Saturday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
