<HEADLINE>
<P>
NHL ROUNDUP; FLAMES END STREAK WITH VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 German Titov and Theoren Fleury scored less than two minutes apart late in the 
third period to give the Calgary Flames a 4-2 victory over the Florida Panthers 
on Friday night at Calgary. 
</P>
<P>
 Gary Roberts and Robert Reichel each had a power-play goal and an assist for 
the Flames, who ended a five-game winless streak one day after acquiring center 
Michael Nylander and defensemen Zarley Zalapski and James Patrick from the 
Hartford Whalers. 
</P>
<P>
 Zalapski and Nylander had assists in their Calgary debut. 
</P>
<P>
 Florida, which has lost nine of its last 12 games, managed only 15 shots on 
goal and remained one point behind the Philadelphia Flyers in the race for the 
final Eastern Conference playoff berth. 
</P>
<P>
 Titov's goal with 5:21 to play broke a 2-2 tie. 
</P>
<P>
 Fleury scored with 3:26 left. 
</P>
<P>
 Vancouver 8, Winnipeg 4 -- Pavel Bure scored three goals against newly 
acquired Jet goaltender Tim Cheveldae at Winnipeg. 
</P>
<P>
 Edmonton 4, Detroit 2 -- Scott Pearson scored the tiebreaking goal 39 seconds 
into the third period and teammate Bill Ranford stopped 45 shots at Edmonton. 
</P>
</TEXT>
