<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOCCER; U.S. WILL PLAY SOUTH KOREA TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE CART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The U.S. national soccer team will play South Korea tonight at 7 at Cal State 
Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 The Americans are coming off a disappointing performance at the Joe Robbie Cup 
in Miami last month. The U.S. team tied Bolivia and lost, 3-1, to Sweden. 
</P>
<P>
 South Korea, which has qualified for this summer's World Cup finals, has been 
training in Los Angeles for two weeks. The two teams scrimmaged last week and 
the United States won, 1-0. 
</P>
<P>
 The U.S. team is 1-3-4 this year. JULIE CART 
</P>
</TEXT>
