<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ciro Ferrara, captain of Napoli and a teammate of Maradona in the late 1980s, 
said Pugliese's allegations were groundless. 
</P>
<P>
 Alan Eagleson, a former head of the NHL players' union who was named in a 
Boston indictment charging him with racketeering, embezzlement and fraud, has 
no intention of turning himself in to U.S. authorities until he gets more 
details about the charges, his lawyers said in Toronto. Track and Field 
</P>
<P>
 Holli Hyche of Indiana State, the outdoor 100- and 200-meter champion, ran a 
meet-record 22.95 seconds in a women's 200 meters semifinal at the NCAA indoor 
track and field championships at Indianapolis. She also won her quarterfinal 
and semifinal heats in the 55 meters, clocking 6.74 and 6.72, respectively. 
</P>
