<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA ANITA; WEKIVA SPRINGS WILL SKIP THE SAN FELIPE STAKES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB MIESZERSKI, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Wekiva Springs, who didn't run in the San Rafael Stakes because of a quarter 
crack in a hoof, won't run in the San Felipe Stakes on March 20. 
</P>
<P>
 "He came out of his (Wednesday) work sore," trainer Bob Hess Jr. said 
Friday."We've X-rayed him all over, but haven't found any problem. By the way 
he was walking after his work, I thought it might be in his knee or shoulder, 
but they haven't been able to pinpoint it." 
</P>
<P>
 A son of Runaway Groom, Wekiva Springs worked seven furlongs in 1:31 3/5 
Wednesday morning. Owned by Donald R. Dizney, he has won three of four starts, 
including the Santa Catalina Stakes on Jan. 22. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Lakeway will try to further solidify her position as the nation's top 
3-year-old filly in the $212,800 Santa Anita Oaks on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Unbeaten in three starts, the daughter of Seattle Slew will have only five 
rivals, including Las Virgenes runner-up Fancy 'N Fabulous, in the 1 1/16-mile 
Oaks. 
</P>
