<HEADLINE>
<P>
'TOO GOOD' TO GET READING AT SCR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAN HERMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 David Ford's "Too Good to Be True" will be given a staged reading at 7:30 p.m. 
Monday at South Coast Repertory, 655 Town Center Drive. The play, about 
employees of a national AIDS charity, won second prize last week in SCR's 
California Playwrights Competition for unproduced scripts. 
</P>
<P>
 Ford, a director and performance artist, lives in Oakland and, according to 
SCR, has collaborated either as director or co-creator of a variety of 
productions in the Bay Area, including "Memory Tricks" with Marga Gomez, which 
won a Bay Area Critics Circle Award and was recently produced at the Public 
Theatre in New York, and "Looking for Black Women on the Radio" with Bill 
Talen. 
</P>
<P>
 The top winner of the SCR competition, "Green Icebergs" by Cecilia Fannon, 
will be given a reading at the theater May 2. Both readings will take place on 
the Mainstage. General admission is $7. (714) 957-4033.JAN HERMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
