ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; KING CASE ATTORNEY WILL LECTURE TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GEOFF BOUCHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The attorney who represented Los Angeles police Officer Laurence M. Powell 
during the Rodney King case will give a free lecture this morning on his 
strategy during the case at the Fullerton campus of Western State University 
College of Law. 
</P>
<P>
 Michael Stone, a Western State graduate, will speak about the landmark case 
and also about the arrival and effect of new courtroom technology such as the 
laser-disc equipment he has used to present visual information to jurors. 
</P>
<P>
 The notorious 88.8-second home video of police officers beating motorist King 
during a traffic stop will be shown, as will some exhibits from the case such 
as a skull replica and photos. 
</P>
<P>
 Stone will also discuss the focus of his career, police law and litigation and 
governmental liability defense. 
</P>
<P>
 The two-hour lecture begins at 10 a.m. at the law college, 1111 N. State 
College Blvd., Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Parking in the school lot will be available. For more information, call (714) 
738-1000. GEOFF BOUCHER 
</P>
