<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: STANTON; FORUM SCHEDULED ON PUBLIC SAFETY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WILLSON CUMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The seven-member Community Safety Advisory Committee, charged with improving 
safety for residents and local businesses, will host a meeting today to hear 
ideas from the public. 
</P>
<P>
 The forum will be from 9 a.m. to noon at the Civic Center, 7800 Katella Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Committee member Harrison Hamada said the group, created in December by the 
City Council, has its final meeting on March 29 and will then make 
recommendations to the council. 
</P>
<P>
 Hamada said the group has met with gang experts, community organizers and 
others from the county and state to develop a plan for a safer community. 
</P>
<P>
 The Orange County Sheriff's Department, which provides police services to 
Stanton, has also been involved in the discussions. 
</P>
<P>
 Hamada said some goals are to ask the council to increase code enforcement, so 
that neighborhoods are maintained in a clean and safe manner. 
</P>
<P>
 He said needs include more outreach to ethnic communities, safety programs for 
seniors, and better disaster preparedness. WILLSON CUMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
