<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: GREEN CONTAINERS JUST FOR TRIMMINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles Bureau of Sanitation is asking all city residents who use yard 
trimming collection services to only put grass, leaves and tree trimmings in 
their green garbage containers. 
</P>
<P>
 Separate yard-trimming collection allows the material to be turned into 
compost instead of ending up in landfills. The compost is sold in Fedco stores 
as TOPGRO, "L.A.'s Own Compost." 
</P>
<P>
 Residents with earthquake debris can call (213) 847-8811 for collection. 
MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
