<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASKETBALL REGIONAL CHAMPIONSHIP GAMES; GIRLS' DIVISION III REGIONAL 
FINAL; NEWPORT HARBOR VS. BREA-OLINDA, 9:30 A.M. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Where--Anaheim Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor (24-7)--Genevieve Evarts has been on fire in the playoffs, and 
she scored a game-high 22 points when the Sailors played Brea a week ago in the 
Southern Section Division III-AA championship game. Evarts isn't the problem. 
Her teammates combined for only 18 points against a Ladycat defense that was 
content to let Newport bring the ball upcourt. In the first game, the Sailors 
thought they could handle the emotional battle of playing Brea and they 
trailed, 17-2, after one quarter. Having lost once before creates an even 
bigger emotional battle. 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda (31-0)--The Ladycats' six playoff victories have been by an 
average of 45 points. Nno team has scored more than 20 points against them by 
halftime, and the Ladycats' average lead has been 32. Sarah Beckley has been 
terrific under the boards in the playoffs. In the midst of a slump in the first 
meeting with Newport Harbor, Nicole Erickson was four of 18 from the field--the 
rest of the team was 23 of 39 (59%). In Thursday's victory over San Luis 
Obispo, Erickson was nine of 11. No slump, no worries. 
</P>
<P>
 Key to the game--Newport Harbor's post play was nonexistent in the first 
game--the Sailors got only two offensive rebounds and 18 total. When Brea broke 
the game open early, eight of its first 12 points came on follow shots. If the 
Sailors don't rebound, they won't win. And even if they do, they have almost no 
chance. Starting Lineups 
</P>
