<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASKETBALL REGIONAL CHAMPIONSHIP GAMES; GIRLS' DIVISION II REGIONAL FINAL; 
MISSION HILLS ALEMANY VS. WOODBRIDGE, 1:30 P.M. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON H. REID 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Where--Anaheim Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 Alemany (30-0)--Alemany is the No. 2-seeded team. The Indians won in the first 
round, 63-53, over Escondido and in the semifinals, 68-51, over San Diego 
Mission Bay.Alemany defeated San Bernardino, 49-46, in the Southern Section 
Division II-A final. Alemany won the division title in 1992 and has won six 
league titles in the last seven seasons. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge (31-0)--Woodbridge is seeded No. 1. The Warriors won in the first 
round, 71-41, over Bakersfield East and in the semifinals, 84-63, over San 
Bernardino. Woodbridge defeated Hemet, 59-47, in the Division II-AA final. 
Woodbridge won the Southern Section II-A title in 1991 and has won nine league 
titles in the past 11 seasons. 
</P>
<P>
 Key to the game--Woodbridge has a quicker backcourt, a deeper bench and has 
played better competition. Warrior guards Jamie Oenning and Erin Stovall are 
athletic and skilled shooters. If they can spark the transition game with 
steals, Woodbridge should be in a good position. Alemany center Carly Funicello 
and forward Samantha Rigley must control the game under the basket or the 
Indians will struggle. This game should provide more of a challenge than either 
team has faced in the regular season or playoffs, but Woodbridge has the edge. 
Starting Lineups 
</P>
<P>
 ALEMANY 04,04,18,06,06 P Name Ht. Avg. F Zevette Mitchell 6-0 10.0 F Samantha 
Rigley 5-10 15.5 C Carly Funicello 6-3 16.0 G Kelly McKay 5-9 12.0 G Jen. 
Stoughton 5-5 1.0 Coach: Melissa Hearlihy WOODBRIDGE 04,04,17,05,06 P Name Ht. 
Avg. F Melanie Pearson 6-1 11.4 C Angela Burgess 6-4 12.7 G Jamie Oenning 5-7 
13.3 G Erin Stovall 5-7 11.1 G Tami Weaver 5-5 7.2  
</P>
<P>
 Coach: Eric Bangs JASON H. REID 
</P>
</TEXT>
